#: ../../source/modules/configuration/notifications/templates.rst:4
msgid ""
"A template is a global object of GLPI that defines the information included "
"in a notification and the formatting of the information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/notifications/templates.rst:6
msgid ""
"The creation of a template is a complex operation, which impacts the users. "
"Therefore, templates can only be modified by Administrators with the "
"*Update* permission for the *Config* right. Moreover a template is not "
"linked to an entity, which means that it is not possible to delegate its "
"management to an administrator of a of a sub-entity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/notifications/templates.rst:10
msgid ""
"A template reflects a communication to a user and can be available in "
"several languages thanks to a translation mechanism. The use of tags (i.e. "
"markers that are independent of the language used) language used) makes it "
"possible to create a generic translation, available for all the languages of"
" GLPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/configuration/notifications/templates.rst:13
msgid ""
"GLPI comes with a set of pre-defined templates for all notifications "
"(tickets, reservations, financial information, cartridges, consumables, "
"licenses, MySQL synchronization ...)."
msgstr ""

